\section*{Introduction}
- In acquired immune response, specific antigens are recognized by
- Antibodies - soluble or transmembrane (BCR)
- TCR
- Antibodies recognize antigens on the outside of pathogens or as soluble materials e.g. toxins
- TCR recognize peptides in the context of MHC molecules on the surface of host cells

\section*{Antigen recognition by antibodies/B cells}
- Recognize molecular shapes (epitopes) on antigens
- Complementary to paratope on Ab
- Abs recognize the topographic surface of a protein Ag
