\section*{MHC}
- Peptides generated by a cytosolic multisubunit proteolytic complex called the proteasome
- The peptides are transported into the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) by the adenosine triphosphate-dependent transporters associated with antigen processing (TAPs), where they associate with MHC I
- When stably assembled, the complexes are transported to the cell surface via the ER and Golgi network

